news.title: Bengaluru: 1,443 litigations of BDA properties pending in court
news.para: The Lokayukta ordered re-list the matter on February 10, 2023. BDA Engineer Member HR Shantharajanna submitted to the Lokayukta that action is being initiated in a phased manner for removal of unauthorised occupation after verifying the pendency of litigations and court orders, if any, passed.

news.title: Homebuyers in Karnataka fight for transparency, clarity
news.para: The jurisdictional Sub-Registrar Officer (SRO) is registering the deed of declaration as required by the KAOA, but they have no authority to register with an apartment owners’ association. Promoters are inserting the by-laws of the association along with the deed of declaration for registration.​

news.title: Energy conservation building code adopted in Tamil Nadu
news.para: The GO dated December 27 said that the government after careful examinations, makes Tamil Nadu Energy Conservation Building Code (TNECBC) 2022 under the Energy Conservation Act.

news.title: HIDCO to e-auction 10-acre land in Kolkata on December 29
news.para: A starting bidding price for the 10-acre land has been fixed at Rs 177.2 crore. The landwill be sold off on a freehold basis for residential or commercial use or for a mix of both the purposes.

news.title: Now, two-year window for builders to reschedule dues in Noida & Greater Noida
news.para: Builders will have to deposit 20% of the total outstanding amount within one month from the date of issue of the reschedulement letter.

news.title: Bank cannot retain amount paid under OTS after having cancelled offer: Karnataka HC
news.para: Allowing the petition filed by M/s Rima Transformers and Conductors Private Limited, Bengaluru, justice M Nagaprasanna has noted that the petitioner’s offer of OTS was accepted by the Canara Bank with certain conditions and the petitioner also accepted the terms and conditions.

news.title: Prabhadevi building gets Bombay HC backing to form housing society
news.para: The Act permits only the promoter or property owner to declare it as a condominium-an alternate form of association of flat owners where the builder has greater rights to open spaces and any additional FSI.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh-RERA hands over stalled project to another developer
news.para: The project in question is ‘Oh My God’, a commercial venture in Noida’s Sector 129 by Baya Weaver Ltd. Work on the project began in April 2015, chasing a February 2023 deadline.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires nine acres of land Gurugram
news.para: This project will offer approximately 1.6 million sq ft of premium residential development and will have an estimated revenue potential of approximately Rs 2,500 crore.

news.title: Two new members join Uttar Pradesh RERA, hearings to gain momentum
news.para: Both the members will be working from the RERA's NCR regional office in Greater Noida, Gautam Buddh Nagar as 75 per cent complaints of UP RERA belong to districts of NCR that includes Gautam Buddh Nagar, Ghaziabad, Meerut, Muzzafarnagar etc, the statement said.

news.title: Land compensation to farmers hiked, scheme for flat registry soon: Noida Authority
news.para: Noida Authority CEO Ritu Maheshwari and Uttar Pradesh Financial Corporation Managing Director Rajshekhar also attended the meeting held here.

news.title: NCDRC directs Raheja Developers to pay Rs 1.19 crore to buyer for delay in delivery
news.para: The NCDRC was hearing a complaint filed by Sunny Ahuja in respect of a plot allotted to him in a project known as 'Raheja Aranya City', Sector 11 and 14, Phase I, Sohna Road, Gurgaon promoted by Raheja Developers.

news.title: Home prices ease to more than five-year low in November in Hong Kong
news.para: November's fall in home prices came after a revised 2.7% drop in October. Home prices in Hong Kong have fallen 13.8% in the first 110 months of the year.

news.title: Housing minister releases guidelines for ranking cities
news.para: City Finance Rankings 2022 aim to evaluate, recognise and reward urban local bodies (ULBs) on the basis of their strength across three financial parameters -- resource mobilisation, expenditure performance and fiscal governance systems.

news.title: India's office market net absorption touch 38.25 million sq. ft in 2022: JLL
news.para: Bengaluru with a 23.7% share retained its leadership position accounting for the highest net absorption for the calendar year 2022, with Hyderabad close behind in the second spot.
